HEADWORD: youth-on-age
<hw>youth`-on-age"</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A vigorous
perennial herb (<spn>Tolmiea menziesii</spn>) with flowers in erect
racemes and having young plants develop at the junction of a leaf blade
and the leafstalk.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pickaback plant, piggyback plant.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Youthsome</ent>⟦br⟧
